  "prompt": "Do wrestlers have to stretch before they workout?",
  "response": "Yes, wrestlers, like most athletes, should stretch before working out to help prevent injuries and improve performance. Stretching provides several benefits:\n\n1. Dynamic stretching before a workout helps:\n- Warm up muscles\n- Increase flexibility\n- Improve range of motion\n- Reduce risk of injury\n- Enhance blood flow to muscles\n\n2. Types of stretching wrestlers typically do:\n- Dynamic stretches (moving stretches)\n- Static stretches\n- Sport-specific mobility exercises\n- Foam rolling\n- Joint mobilization\n\n3. Specific areas wrestlers focus on stretching:\n- Shoulders\n- Neck\n- Back\n- Hips\n- Legs\n- Ankles\n\n4. Recommended stretching routine:\n- Light cardio warm-up\n- Dynamic stretching\n- Sport-specific movement drills\n\nStretching is crucial for wrestlers to maintain flexibility, prevent muscle strains, and prepare their body for the intense physical demands of training and competition.",
